ec85b1e2-b0b5-425c-8dde-2aab03665e40.4175a01e-c88b-4fce-8ae7-0a7057833d90.description=
Reads the file specified in the source input parameter.  
If Store is true, then all matching lines are pushed into the Session and then subsequent calls
to the operation results in the next line being returned.

Input Parameters\:
Source - path to the file to be read
Filter - regular expression filter to be applied to each line (can be left blank for all)
Store - (true,false) whether to store results in the session for retrieval
delimiter - If set to null, the file is read line by line, otherwise it is a delimiter placed between read lines (note, the entire file may or may not still be fully read at once, depending on size).
user - alternate credentials username
password - alternate credentials password
eofReset - If set to true than after the No More response has been returned once, the operation will restart reading the file from the beginning on the next call.
characterSet - The character encoding used to read the file (for instance, windows-1252). The default is UTF-8.

Responses\:
more lines - more lines are available to be read in the session
no more lines - no lines are available for reading in the session

Extra Results\:
COUNT - on the first pass, the total number of lines matched.  on subsequent runs, the number of lines remaining in the session. This result is only returned in line-by-line mode.
ec85b1e2-b0b5-425c-8dde-2aab03665e40.5e58f9a7-b911-4627-93d8-77a39c596589.description=
Adds flow variables into the local context (available to itself and child flows only)

Input Parameters\:
keyNames - the names of the flow variables to use
myValues - the values to assign the flow variables
delimiter - a delimiter separating values and keys.

Responses\:
success - assigned the flow variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];
ec85b1e2-b0b5-425c-8dde-2aab03665e40.7826c29a-a3ea-4134-841f-45895b08835d.description=
Runs a SQL SELECT query.
Returns the complete result like the following\:
a1b2

Inputs\:
    DBServerName - The hostname or ip address of db server.
    DbType - The type of database to connect to. 
Valid values\: Oracle, MSSQL, Sybase, Netcool, DB2 and Custom.
Default value\: Oracle
    Username - The username to use when connecting to the server.
    Password -  The password to use when connecting to the server.
    instance - The name instance of MSSQL Server. Leave it blank for default instance.
    DbPort - The port to connect to.
Default values\: Oracle\: 1521, MSSQL\: 1433, Sybase\: 5000, Netcool\: 4100, DB2\: 50000.
    Database - The name of the database.
    authenticationType - The type of authentication used to access the database (applicable only to MSSQL type). 
Valid values\: sql, windows (for MSSQL)
Default value\: sql
    Command - The command to execute.
    colDelimiter - The delimiter to use between columns in resulting table.
Default value\: comma (,)
    rowDelimiter - The delimiter to use between rows in resulting table.
Default value\: \n
    timeout - Seconds to wait before timing out the SQL command execution.
Default value\: 0 

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. Return the list of all the data returned by the query. It is delimited by colDelimiter and rowDelimiter. 

Responses\:
    success - The command was executed successfully. 
    failure - Failed to execute the command. 

Note\: 
SQL statement other than SELECT statement (like INSERT, UPDATE or DELETE) is not supported. In case statements other than SELECT are executed then the operation will fail but the statements might get partially or fully executed in the database.

ec85b1e2-b0b5-425c-8dde-2aab03665e40.94e12d35-1ea9-46fe-a6e5-1388bfa045f0.description=
Check the current date and time, and returns a java DateAndTime formatted string of it. If locale is specified, it will return the date and time string based on the locale.Otherwise, default locale will be used.

Inputs\:
localeLang - The locale language for date and time string. For example,  en or ja.
localeCountry - The locale country for date and time string. For example, US or JP. If localeLang is not specified, this input will be ingored.

Result\:
Current date and time.

Responses\:
success - Date/time retrieved successfully.
failure - Date/time could not be retrieved.

ec85b1e2-b0b5-425c-8dde-2aab03665e40.cf19a570-57c4-458a-a205-8a2ad04e19b4.description= 
Gets a list of files and folders in a directory.

Input Parameters\:
Source - the directory to check
delimiter - A delimiter to put between files and folders in the directory.
user         - username to use when reading.
password - password to use when reading.

returns\:
The children of the path.

Extra Results\:
count - the number of children.

Responses\:
failure			- the operation failed. The path probably could not be found, or was a file.
success			- The operation succeeded.
